title: The Appeal to Nature Fallacy (vegan / vegans / veganism)
description: This has become a popular idea (really just used as an insult), but (1) not every use of the concept of nature is a fallacy, and (2) in practice, it may not be useful at all to snub someone by telling them that they're lapsing into "an appeal-to-nature fallacy" even if they actually are.
